    <br>(b) Find the equation of the line perpendicular to PQ passing through R(0 ; −1). <span class="marks-badge">3</span></div>
    <button class="memo-toggle" onclick="toggleMemo(this)">📋 Show Memo</button>
    <div class="memo-content">
      <strong>(a)</strong> θ = 45° → m = tan45° = 1<br>
      m = (5−k)/(3−1) = 1 → 5−k = 2 → k = 3 ✓ (3)<br><br>
      <strong>(b)</strong> m_perp = −1 (since m_PQ × m_perp = −1)<br>
