  <div style="margin-bottom:10px;font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:1.2rem;color:var(--pink);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);padding-bottom:8px;margin-top:30px">QUESTION 2 — Trigonometry [50]</div>

  <div class="q-block">
    <div class="q-num">Q2.1</div>
    <div class="q-text">Without using a calculator, simplify each of the following:
    <br>(a) sin(180°+θ)·cos(360°−θ) / [tan(180°−θ)·sin(−θ)] <span class="marks-badge">6</span>
    <br>(b) cos(90°+x)·sin(90°−x) + sin²(180°+x) <span class="marks-badge">4</span></div>
    <button class="memo-toggle" onclick="toggleMemo(this)">📋 Show Memo</button>
    <div class="memo-content">
      <strong>(a)</strong> sin(180°+θ) = −sinθ<br>
      cos(360°−θ) = cosθ<br>
      tan(180°−θ) = −tanθ<br>
      sin(−θ) = −sinθ<br>
      = (−sinθ)(cosθ) / [(−tanθ)(−sinθ)]<br>
      = −sinθ·cosθ / (tanθ·sinθ)<br>
      = −cosθ / tanθ = −cosθ / (sinθ/cosθ)<br>
      = −cos²θ/sinθ ✓ (6)<br><br>
      <strong>(b)</strong> cos(90°+x) = −sinx; sin(90°−x) = cosx; sin(180°+x) = −sinx<br>
      = (−sinx)(cosx) + (−sinx)²<br>
      = −sinx·cosx + sin²x ✓ (4)
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-block">
    <div class="q-num">Q2.2</div>
    <div class="q-text">Prove the following identities:
    <br>(a) (1 − sin²θ)/cosθ = cosθ <span class="marks-badge">3</span>
    <br>(b) sin²α/(1 − cosα) = 1 + cosα <span class="marks-badge">4</span>
    <br>(c) (sinβ + cosβ)² = 1 + 2sinβcosβ <span class="marks-badge">3</span></div>
    <button class="memo-toggle" onclick="toggleMemo(this)">📋 Show Memo</button>
    <div class="memo-content">
      <strong>(a)</strong> LHS = cos²θ/cosθ = cosθ = RHS ✓ (3)<br><br>
      <strong>(b)</strong> LHS = (1−cos²α)/(1−cosα) = [(1−cosα)(1+cosα)]/(1−cosα) = 1+cosα = RHS ✓ (4)<br><br>
      <strong>(c)</strong> LHS = sin²β + 2sinβcosβ + cos²β = 1 + 2sinβcosβ = RHS ✓ (3)
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-block">
    <div class="q-num">Q2.3</div>
    <div class="q-text">Determine the general solution of each equation:
